      "Useful outputs: personalized prompts, better recommendations (books, games, events, gifts), and better self-understanding over time.",
      "Sources: Hacker News, Reddit, personal website sitemap, X/Twitter, Google Keep, Obsidian, ChatGPT/Claude/Perplexity/TypingMind logs, Readwise, Instapaper.",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Smart Bookmarking Extension (.forsale.com)",
    description:
      "Browser extension that lets users save any page instantly. Backend parses page text, summarizes it, tags it, and stores embeddings for semantic search.",
    notes: [
      "Ingestion flow: fetch page -> extract text (BeautifulSoup/Jina Reader) -> summarize -> auto-tag -> embed.",
      "Could expose timeline views, topic clusters, and memory recall across saved links.",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Async Book Club",
    description:
      "Book discussion forum with asynchronous threads (no mandatory Zoom). One book post, unlimited long-form discussion.",
    notes: ["Could be built on top of Discourse for a fast MVP."],
  },
  {
    title: "ICP Suggester",
    description:
      "Tool that analyzes a business and suggests ultra-niche ICPs/MCPs with structured output for prospecting workflows.",
    notes: [
      "Flow: analyze site -> detect product category -> suggest ICP slices -> export for outreach tools.",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Email Warmup Tool",
    description:
      "Not groundbreaking, but durable. Compete on pricing and network size. A larger email network should improve warmup quality.",
    notes: ["Potential wedge: free tier to grow the sender network quickly."],
  },
];

